/* rounded-nested — concentric corner for a rounded child in a rounded overflow-clipped container (hovered list row, tab pill); container clips children at padding-box corner (radius−border-width), else child's corner slices into a square "ear".
 * Derives child radius: container corner − child's gap to edge − --nest-safe (sub-pixel guard; clipped container uses ring not border, clips at full radius) — guaranteed clearance instead of a guessed literal.
